        <mxCell id="n88" value="The rule that holds across every phase" style="text;html=1;fontSize=13;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#FFFFFF;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="790" width="900" height="20" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n89" value="An approved request becomes a CONFIGURATION ROW executed by ONE generic engine. MFT, API, mashup or event — it never generates a new Boomi component per interface. Cut scope from the form before you cut it from the automation." style="text;html=1;fontSize=12;fontColor=#B9C4D0;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="810" width="1460" height="24" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n90" value="" style="rounded=1;arcSize=6;html=1;fillColor=#FFFFFF;strokeColor=#DFE4EA;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="40" y="868" width="1500" height="124" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n91" value="Three decisions that need a named owner BEFORE Phase 0 starts" style="text;html=1;fontSize=13;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#8F1D17;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="876" width="900" height="20" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n92" value="1.  May the MVP provision a PRODUCTION interface on a username and password?  Recommendation: no — gate Production until SSO lands in Phase 3, or pull SSO forward and accept the delay." style="text;html=1;fontSize=11.5;fontColor=#3D4653;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="900" width="1460" height="24" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n93" value="2.  Do Phases 2 and 3 swap?  API build lands before enterprise SSO and the full pre-check engine. Defensible for a governed pilot; uncomfortable for an API estate. SRO decision." style="text;html=1;fontSize=11.5;fontColor=#3D4653;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="926" width="1460" height="24" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n94" value="3.  Will the mashup engine be held to DECLARATIVE composition?  The first request for an arbitrary script inside a mashup arrives around month four. Decide the answer now, not then." style="text;html=1;fontSize=11.5;fontColor=#3D4653;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="60" y="952" width="1460" height="24" as="geometry"/></mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
</mxfile>
